genresAdvancedInfo.name: historic string quartet
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre features the performance of classical music pieces by a group of four string instruments - two violins, a viola, and a cello. The music is played on vintage instruments that were popular in the past, and the quartet aims to recreate the original sound and style of the composer. The music is characterized by its intricate harmonies, emotional depth, and virtuosity.
